      ],
      "parameters": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A string used in debugging to indicate the reason the activity began. This parameter must not be ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "nil",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " or an empty string.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "reason"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A block containing the work to be performed by the activity. The block has no return value and takes the following parameter:",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            },
            {
              "items": [
                {
                  "definition": {
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "inlineContent": [
                          {
                            "text": "A Boolean indicating whether the process is about to be suspended. If the value is ",
                            "type": "text"
                          },
                          {
                            "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/swift/true",
                            "isActive": false,
                            "type": "reference"
                          },
                          {
                            "text": ", the process is about to be suspended so you should take whatever steps are needed to stop in progress work. If it is ",
                            "type": "text"
                          },
                          {
                            "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/swift/false",
                            "isActive": false,
                            "type": "reference"
                          },
                          {
                            "text": ", start the planned tasks.",
                            "type": "text"
                          }
                        ],
                        "type": "paragraph"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  "term": {
                    "inlineContent": [
                      {
                        "text": "expired",
                        "type": "text"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                }
              ],
              "type": "termList"
            }
          ],
          "name": "block"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Use this method to perform tasks when your process is executing in the background. This method queues ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "block",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " for asynchronous execution on a concurrent queue. When your process is in the background, the method tries to take a task assertion to ensure that your block has time to execute. If it is unable to take a task assertion, or if the time allotted for the task assertion expires, the system executes your block with the parameter set to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/swift/true",
              "isActive": false,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". If it is able to take the task assertion, it executes the block and passes ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/swift/false",
              "isActive": false,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " for the expired parameter. ",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If your block is still executing and the system need to suspend the process, the system executes your block a second time with the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "expired",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " parameter set to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/swift/true",
              "isActive": false,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". Your block must be prepared to handle this case. When the expired parameter is ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/swift/true",
              "isActive": false,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ", stop any in-progress tasks as quickly as possible. ",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
